						<summary>

						<p>On the same pillar-Museum Acc. No. 81.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1067 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The top portion on the first face (actual III face of the pillar) seems to be a continuation of the previous record. It begins abruptly. It mentions Koḷapāka as the capital and registers a grant made on <hi rend="italic">uttarāyaṇa saṁkrānti</hi> to the god Svayaṁbhu Sōmēśvara of Koḷapāka by Śrī Trailōkyamalla Rebbiseṭṭi and the <hi rend="italic">nakara</hi> (of the place).</p>						

						<p>Though engraved separately and being a continuation part this portion of the record can be ascribed to the date of the previous record (No. 33).</p>						

						</summary>
